The paper deals with the computational complexity of the exponential random graph model (ERGM) commonly used in social network analysis. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The paper also involves graph theory and probability, which suggests cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.SD (Systems and Control) as possible categories. The use of standard feature types based on sociological theories suggests cs.CC (Computational Complexity) as another possible category. Finally, the paper involves statistical inference and machine learning, which suggests cs.LG (Machine Learning) as a possible category.
